the pines with the setting sun upon
them, the sinking campfire,

3212
03:00:46,438 --> 03:00:50,745
and now the sound of the water as it
flowed murmuring by the

3213
03:00:50,745 --> 03:00:51,383
shores of the island.

3214
03:00:51,383 --> 03:00:54,910
The tent opened to the east,
and from it they watched

3215
03:00:54,910 --> 03:00:57,792
together their first sunrise.

3216
03:00:57,792 --> 03:01:01,649
In his thoughts he had seen this morning
beforehand also: the waking,

3217
03:01:01,649 --> 03:01:06,200
the gentle sound of the water murmuring
ceaselessly, the growing day,

3218
03:01:06,200 --> 03:01:09,504
the vision of the stream,
the sense that the world was shut

3219
03:01:09,504 --> 03:01:10,887
away far from them.

3220
03:01:10,887 --> 03:01:14,576
So did it all happen,
except that he whispered to her again:⁠—

3221
03:01:14,576 --> 03:01:17,024
“Better than my dreams.”

3222
03:01:17,024 --> 03:01:21,144
They saw the sunlight begin upon a
hilltop; and presently came the sun

3223
03:01:21,144 --> 03:01:27,681
itself, and lakes of warmth flowed into
the air, slowly filling

3224
03:01:27,681 --> 03:01:29,774
the green solitude.

3225
03:01:29,774 --> 03:01:35,875
Along the island shores the ripples
caught flashes from the sun.

3226
03:01:35,875 --> 03:01:39,637
“I am going into the stream,”
he said to her; and rising,

3227
03:01:39,637 --> 03:01:40,905
he left her in the tent.

3228
03:01:40,905 --> 03:01:44,499
This was his side of the island,
he had told her last night;

3229
03:01:44,499 --> 03:01:48,456
the other was hers, where he had made a
place for her to bathe.

3230
03:01:48,456 --> 03:01:54,635
When he was gone, she found it,
walking through the trees and rocks

3231
03:01:54,635 --> 03:01:56,109
to the water’s edge.

3232
03:01:56,109 --> 03:02:01,063
And so, with the island between them,
the two bathed in the cold stream.

3233
03:02:01,063 --> 03:02:05,227
When he came back, he found her already
busy at their camp.

3234
03:02:05,227 --> 03:02:09,302
The blue smoke of the fire was floating
out from the trees, loitering

3235
03:02:09,302 --> 03:02:13,123
undispersed in the quiet air,
and she was getting their breakfast.

3236
03:02:13,123 --> 03:02:16,697
She had been able to forestall him
because he had delayed long at his

3237
03:02:16,697 --> 03:02:20,757
dressing, not willing to
return to her unshaven.

3238
03:02:20,757 --> 03:02:24,710
She looked at his eyes that were clear as
the water he had leaped into,

3239
03:02:24,710 --> 03:02:28,907
and at his soft silk
neckerchief, knotted with care.

3240
03:02:28,907 --> 03:02:31,252
“Do not let us ever go away from here!”

3241
03:02:31,252 --> 03:02:34,594
she cried, and ran to him as he came.

3242
03:02:34,594 --> 03:02:38,349
They sat long together at breakfast,
breathing the morning breath of the

3243
03:02:38,349 --> 03:02:43,407
earth that was fragrant with woodland
moisture and with the pines.

3244
03:02:43,407 --> 03:02:46,691
After the meal he could not prevent her
helping him make everything clean.

3245
03:02:46,691 --> 03:02:51,276
Then, by all customs of mountain
journeys, it was time they should break

3246
03:02:51,276 --> 03:02:55,147
camp and be moving before the
heat of the day.

3247
03:02:55,147 --> 03:03:00,394
But first, they delayed for no reason,
save that in these hours they so

3248
03:03:00,394 --> 03:03:02,266
loved to do nothing.

3249
03:03:02,266 --> 03:03:08,102
And next, when with some energy he got
upon his feet and declared he must go

3250
03:03:08,102 --> 03:03:11,488
and drive the horses in, she asked, Why?

3251
03:03:11,488 --> 03:03:14,606
Would it not be well for him to fish
here, that they might be sure of

3252
03:03:14,606 --> 03:03:15,848
trout at their nooning?

3253
03:03:15,848 --> 03:03:21,839
And though he knew that where they should
stop for noon, trout would be as sure as

3254
03:03:21,839 --> 03:03:24,770
here, he took this chance for more
delay.

3255
03:03:24,770 --> 03:03:28,506
She went with him to his fishing rock,
and sat watching him.

3256
03:03:28,506 --> 03:03:32,427
The rock was tall, higher than his
head when he stood.

3257
03:03:32,427 --> 03:03:36,634
It jutted out halfway across the stream,
and the water flowed round it in quick

3258
03:03:36,634 --> 03:03:39,016
foam, and fell into a pool.

3259
03:03:39,016 --> 03:03:40,379
He caught several fish;

3260
03:03:40,379 --> 03:03:45,159
but the sun was getting high,
and after a time it was plain the fish

3261
03:03:45,159 --> 03:03:46,547
had ceased to rise.

3262
03:03:46,547 --> 03:03:54,008
Yet still he stood casting in silence,
while she sat by and watched him.

3263
03:03:54,008 --> 03:03:58,383
Across the stream, the horses wandered or
lay down in their pasture.

3264
03:03:58,383 --> 03:04:03,100
At length he said with half a sigh that
perhaps they ought to go.

3265
03:04:03,100 --> 03:04:03,740
“Ought?”

3266
03:04:03,740 --> 03:04:05,519
she repeated softly.

3267
03:04:05,519 --> 03:04:08,387
“If we are to get anywhere
today,” he answered.

3268
03:04:08,387 --> 03:04:09,682
“Need we get anywhere?”

3269
03:04:09,682 --> 03:04:10,431
she asked.

3270
03:04:10,431 --> 03:04:13,566
Her question sent delight through
him like a flood.

3271
03:04:13,566 --> 03:04:16,281
“Then you do not want to move camp today?”

3272
03:04:16,281 --> 03:04:17,180
said he.

3273
03:04:17,180 --> 03:04:18,793
She shook her head.

3274
03:04:18,793 --> 03:04:24,485
At this he laid down his rod and came
and sat by her.

3275
03:04:24,485 --> 03:04:28,453
“I am very glad we shall not go
till tomorrow,” he murmured.

3276
03:04:28,453 --> 03:04:31,278
“Not tomorrow,” she said.

3277
03:04:31,278 --> 03:04:33,245
“Nor next day.

3278
03:04:33,245 --> 03:04:36,191
Nor any day until we must.”

3279
03:04:36,191 --> 03:04:40,741
And she stretched her hands out to the
island and the stream exclaiming,

3280
03:04:40,741 --> 03:04:42,684
“Nothing can surpass this!”

3281
03:04:42,684 --> 03:04:43,949
He took her in his arms.

3282
03:04:43,949 --> 03:04:47,081
“You feel about it the way I
do,” he almost whispered.

3283
03:04:47,081 --> 03:04:51,843
“I could not have hoped there’d be two of
us to care so much.”

3284
03:04:51,843 --> 03:04:57,419
Presently, while they remained without
speaking by the pool,

3285
03:04:57,419 --> 03:05:00,892
came a little wild animal swimming round
the rock from above.

3286
03:05:00,892 --> 03:05:05,566
It had not seen them,
nor suspected their presence.

3287
03:05:05,566 --> 03:05:09,162
They held themselves still,
watching its alert head cross through

3288
03:05:09,162 --> 03:05:16,381
the waves quickly and come down through
the pool, and so swim to the other side.

3289
03:05:16,381 --> 03:05:21,270
There it came out on a small stretch of
sand, turned its gray head and its

3290
03:05:21,270 --> 03:05:26,798
pointed black nose this way and that,
never seeing them, and then rolled upon

3291
03:05:26,798 --> 03:05:29,143
its back in the warm dry sand.

3292
03:05:29,143 --> 03:05:32,418
After a minute of rolling,
it got on its feet again,

3293
03:05:32,418 --> 03:05:34,562
shook its fur, and trotted away.

3294
03:05:34,562 --> 03:05:39,404
Then the bridegroom husband opened his
shy heart deep down.

3295
03:05:39,404 --> 03:05:42,215
“I am like that fellow,” he said dreamily.

3296
03:05:42,215 --> 03:05:43,986
“I have often done the same.”

3297
03:05:43,986 --> 03:05:49,525
And stretching slowly his arms and legs,
he lay full length upon his back,

3298
03:05:49,525 --> 03:05:51,982
letting his head rest upon her.

3299
03:05:51,982 --> 03:05:56,245
“If I could talk his animal language,
I could talk to him,” he pursued.

3300
03:05:56,245 --> 03:06:00,550
“And he would say to me:
‘Come and roll on the sands.

3301
03:06:00,550 --> 03:06:02,068
Where’s the use of fretting?

3302
03:06:02,068 --> 03:06:04,128
What’s the gain in being a man?

3303
03:06:04,128 --> 03:06:05,735
Come roll on the sands with me.’

3304
03:06:05,735 --> 03:06:06,950
That’s what he would say.”

3305
03:06:06,950 --> 03:06:07,350
The Virginian paused.

3306
03:06:07,350 --> 03:06:11,881
“But,” he continued, “the trouble
is, I am responsible.

3307
03:06:11,881 --> 03:06:15,105
If that could only be forgot forever
by you and me!”

3308
03:06:15,105 --> 03:06:18,803
Again he paused and went
on, always dreamily.

3309
03:06:18,803 --> 03:06:22,817
“Often when I have camped here,
it has made me want to become the

3310
03:06:22,817 --> 03:06:28,400
ground, become the water,
become the trees, mix

3311
03:06:28,400 --> 03:06:29,782
with the whole thing.

3312
03:06:29,782 --> 03:06:32,171
Not know myself from it.

3313
03:06:32,171 --> 03:06:34,971
Never unmix again.

3314
03:06:34,971 --> 03:06:36,874
Why is that?”

3315
03:06:36,874 --> 03:06:42,214
he demanded, looking at her.

3316
03:06:42,214 --> 03:06:43,956
“What is it?

3317
03:06:43,956 --> 03:06:47,968
You don’t know, nor I don’t.

3318
03:06:47,968 --> 03:06:50,528
I wonder would everybody
feel that way here?”

3319
03:06:50,528 --> 03:06:53,795
“I think not everybody,” she answered.

3320
03:06:53,795 --> 03:06:58,075
“No; none except the ones who understand
things they can’t put words to.

3321
03:06:58,075 --> 03:06:59,204
But you did!”

3322
03:06:59,204 --> 03:07:02,468
He put up a hand and touched her softly.

3323
03:07:02,468 --> 03:07:05,520
“You understood about this place.

3324
03:07:05,520 --> 03:07:10,680
And that’s what makes it⁠—makes you and
me as we are now⁠—better than my dreams.

3325
03:07:10,680 --> 03:07:12,769
And my dreams were pretty good.”

3326
03:07:12,769 --> 03:07:17,634
He sighed with supreme quiet and
happiness, and seemed to stretch his

3327
03:07:17,634 --> 03:07:19,484
length closer to the earth.

3328
03:07:19,484 --> 03:07:23,994
And so he lay, and talked to her as he
had never talked to anyone,

3329
03:07:23,994 --> 03:07:25,663
not even to himself.

3330
03:07:25,663 --> 03:07:30,474
Thus she learned secrets of his heart new
to her: his visits here,

3331
03:07:30,474 --> 03:07:33,314
what they were to him,
and why he had chosen it

3332
03:07:33,314 --> 03:07:34,736
for their bridal camp.

3333
03:07:34,736 --> 03:07:38,334
“What I did not know at all,”
he said, “was the way a man can be

3334
03:07:38,334 --> -1:59:59,000
pining for⁠—for this⁠—and never guess
what is the matter with him

3335
-1:59:59,000 --> -1:59:59,000
.

3336
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3337
03:07:42,170 --> 03:07:46,469
When he had finished talking,
still he lay extended and serene;

3338
03:07:46,469 --> 03:07:49,835
and she looked down at him and the
wonderful change that had come over

3339
03:07:49,835 --> 03:07:51,637
him, like a sunrise.

3340
03:07:51,637 --> 03:07:55,890
Was this dreamy boy the man
of two days ago?

3341
03:07:55,890 --> 03:07:59,716
It seemed a distance immeasurable;
yet it was two days only since that

3342
03:07:59,716 --> 03:08:05,416
wedding eve when she had shrunk from him
as he stood fierce and implacable.

3343
03:08:05,416 --> 03:08:09,450
She could look back at that dark hour
now, although she could not speak of it.

3344
03:08:09,450 --> 03:08:14,896
She had seen destruction like sharp steel
glittering in his eyes.

3345
03:08:14,896 --> 03:08:16,807
Were these the same eyes?

3346
03:08:16,807 --> 03:08:23,390
Was this youth with his black head of
hair in her lap the creature with whom

3347
03:08:23,390 --> 03:08:28,511
men did not trifle, whose hand knew
how to deal death?

3348
03:08:28,511 --> 03:08:34,672
Where had the man melted away
to in this boy?

3349
03:08:34,672 --> 03:08:39,168
For as she looked at him,
he might have been no

3350
03:08:39,168 --> 03:08:41,568
older than nineteen today.

3351
03:08:41,568 --> 03:08:46,750
Not even at their first meeting⁠—that
night when his freakish spirit was

3352
03:08:46,750 --> 03:08:48,943
uppermost⁠—had he looked so young.

3353
03:08:48,943 --> 03:08:52,510
This change their hours upon the island
had wrought, filling

3354
03:08:52,510 --> 03:08:56,134
his face with innocence.

3355
03:08:56,134 --> 03:08:59,741
By and by they made their nooning.

3356
03:08:59,741 --> 03:09:04,523
In the afternoon she would have explored
the nearer woods with him,

3357
03:09:04,523 --> 03:09:06,316
or walked up the stream.

3358
03:09:06,316 --> 03:09:10,259
But since this was to be their camp
during several days,

3359
03:09:10,259 --> 03:09:11,575
he made it more complete.

3360
03:09:11,575 --> 03:09:17,479
He fashioned a rough bench and a table;
around their tent he built a tall

3361
03:09:17,479 --> 03:09:22,712
windbreak for better shelter in case of
storm; and for the fire he gathered and

3362
03:09:22,712 --> 03:09:25,287
cut much wood, and piled it up.

3363
03:09:25,287 --> 03:09:29,233
So they were provided for,
and so for six days and nights they

3364
03:09:29,233 --> 03:09:33,812
stayed, finding no day
or night long enough.

3365
03:09:33,812 --> 03:09:37,357
Once his hedge of boughs did them good
service, for they had an

3366
03:09:37,357 --> 03:09:39,277
afternoon of furious storm.

3367
03:09:39,277 --> 03:09:44,690
The wind rocked the pines and ransacked
the island, the sun went out,

3368
03:09:44,690 --> 03:09:48,329
the black clouds rattled,
and white bolts of lightning

3369
03:09:48,329 --> 03:09:49,537
fell close by.

3370
03:09:49,537 --> 03:09:53,951
The shower broke through the pine
branches and poured upon the tent.

3371
03:09:53,951 --> 03:09:58,309
But he had removed everything inside from
where it could touch the canvas and so

3372
03:09:58,309 --> 03:10:01,390
lead the water through,
and the rain ran off into the ditch he

3373
03:10:01,390 --> 03:10:02,896
had dug round the tent.

3374
03:10:02,896 --> 03:10:06,700
While they sat within,
looking out upon the bounding floods and

3375
03:10:06,700 --> 03:10:09,420
the white lightning,
she saw him glance at her

3376
03:10:09,420 --> 03:10:12,742
apprehensively, and at once
she answered his glance.

3377
03:10:12,742 --> 03:10:14,733
“I am not afraid,” she said.

3378
03:10:14,733 --> 03:10:18,221
“If a flame should consume us together
now, what would it matter?”

3379
03:10:18,221 --> 03:10:22,932
And so they sat watching the storm till
it was over, he with his face changed by

3380
03:10:22,932 --> 03:10:25,262
her to a boy’s, and she
leavened with him.

3381
03:10:25,262 --> 03:10:29,253
When at last they were compelled to leave
the island, or see no more of the

3382
03:10:29,253 --> 03:10:32,659
mountains, it was not a final parting.

3383
03:10:32,659 --> 03:10:36,121
They would come back for the last night
before their journey ended.

3384
03:10:36,121 --> 03:10:39,828
Furthermore, they promised each other
like two children to come here every

3385
03:10:39,828 --> 03:10:43,203
year upon their wedding day,
and like two children they believed that

3386
03:10:43,203 --> 03:10:45,108
this would be possible.

3387
03:10:45,108 --> 03:10:51,991
But in after years they did come,
more than once, to keep their wedding

3388
03:10:51,991 --> 03:10:56,174
day upon the island,
and upon each new visit were able to say

3389
03:10:56,174 --> 03:11:00,351
to each other, “Better than our dreams.”

3390
03:11:00,351 --> 03:11:07,445
For thirty days by the light of the sun
and the campfire light they saw no faces

3391
03:11:07,445 --> 03:11:11,493
except their own; and when they were
silent it was all stillness,

3392
03:11:11,493 --> 03:11:16,960
unless the wind passed among the pines,
or some flowing water was near them.

3393
03:11:16,960 --> 03:11:21,683
Sometimes at evening they came upon elk,
or black-tailed deer,

3394
03:11:21,683 --> 03:11:26,657
feeding out in the high parks of the
mountains; and once from the edge of

3395
03:11:26,657 --> 03:11:31,985
some concealing timber he showed her a
bear, sitting with an old log

3396
03:11:31,985 --> 03:11:33,831
lifted in its paws.

3397
03:11:33,831 --> 03:11:37,124
She forbade him to kill the bear,
or any creature that

3398
03:11:37,124 --> 03:11:38,390
they did not require.

3399
03:11:38,390 --> 03:11:43,846
He took her upward by trail and canyon,
through the unfooted woods and along

3400
03:11:43,846 --> 03:11:49,407
dwindling streams to their headwaters,
lakes lying near the summit of the

3401
03:11:49,407 --> 03:11:54,433
range, full of trout,
with meadows of long grass and a

3402
03:11:54,433 --> 03:12:00,595
thousand flowers, and above these the
pinnacles of rock and snow.

3403
03:12:00,595 --> 03:12:05,630
They made their camps in many places,
delaying several days here,

3404
03:12:05,630 --> 03:12:10,078
and one night there,
exploring the high solitudes together,

3405
03:12:10,078 --> 03:12:12,166
and sinking deep in their romance.

3406
03:12:12,166 --> 03:12:17,158
Sometimes when he was at work with their
horses, or intent on casting his brown

3407
03:12:17,158 --> 03:12:22,003
hackle for a fish, she would watch him
with eyes that were fuller of

3408
03:12:22,003 --> 03:12:24,091
love than of understanding.

3409
03:12:24,091 --> 03:12:28,124
Perhaps she never came wholly to
understand him; but in her complete love

3410
03:12:28,124 --> 03:12:29,933
for him she found enough.

3411
03:12:29,933 --> 03:12:32,610
He loved her with his whole man’s power.

3412
03:12:32,610 --> 03:12:36,564
She had listened to him tell her in words
of transport, “I could enjoy dying”; yet

3413
03:12:36,564 --> 03:12:38,089
she loved him more than that.

3414
03:12:38,089 --> 03:12:42,574
He had come to her from a smoking pistol,
able to bid her farewell⁠—and she could

3415
03:12:42,574 --> 03:12:43,595
not let him go.

3416
03:12:43,595 --> 03:12:48,788
At the last white-hot edge of ordeal,
it was she who renounced,

3417
03:12:48,788 --> 03:12:50,908
and he who had his way.

3418
03:12:50,908 --> 03:12:56,959
Nevertheless she found much more than
enough, in spite of the sigh that now

3419
03:12:56,959 --> 03:13:03,484
and again breathed through her happiness
when she would watch him with eyes

3420
03:13:03,484 --> 03:13:07,443
fuller of love than of understanding.

3421
03:13:07,443 --> 03:13:11,289
They could not speak of that grim wedding
eve for a long while after;

3422
03:13:11,289 --> 03:13:18,288
but the mountains brought them together
upon all else in the world

3423
03:13:18,288 --> 03:13:20,120
and their own lives.

3424
03:13:20,120 --> 03:13:24,176
At the end they loved each other doubly
more than at the beginning,

3425
03:13:24,176 --> 03:13:28,790
because of these added confidences which
they exchanged and shared.

3426
03:13:28,790 --> 03:13:33,967
It was a new bliss to her to know a man’s
talk and thoughts, to be given so much

3427
03:13:33,967 --> 03:13:38,598
of him; and to him it was a bliss still
greater to melt from that reserve his

3428
03:13:38,598 --> 03:13:40,924
lonely life had bred in him.

3429
03:13:40,924 --> 03:13:44,371
He never would have guessed so much had
been stored away in him,

3430
03:13:44,371 --> 03:13:46,228
unexpressed till now.

3431
03:13:46,228 --> 03:13:50,339
They did not want to go to Vermont and
leave these mountains,

3432
03:13:50,339 --> 03:13:54,202
but the day came when they had to turn
their backs upon their dream.

3433
03:13:54,202 --> 03:13:58,106
So they came out into the plains once
more, well established in their

3434
03:13:58,106 --> 03:14:03,587
familiarity, with only the journey still
lying between themselves and Bennington.

